			  	Dying is frustrating. U gotta restart everything from scratch.<br />
<br />
Right now, having allied fleets to help defend keeps defleeted players alive. If u allow allied fleets to attack, then its almost guaranteed that a defleeted player will die. Lower members of the attacking council can borrow fleets to take out the defender's borrowed fleets.<br />
<br />
Personally, I'd vote to have game mechanics biased towards keeping ppl alive, instead of biased towards getting them killed.<p><br>______________________________________<br />
